1
00:00:01,360 --> 00:00:03,230
Why don't we go over there together?

2
00:00:03,900 --> 00:00:05,820
A hotel?!

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:09,440
Wow!

4
00:00:09,860 --> 00:00:12,190
Kamo-kun, you're pretty good with your hands!

5
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:15,520
How did you do these super detailed parts?

6
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:19,700
I just figured ladies would probably prefer Western-style castles.

7
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,010
She meant the beach right in front of the hotel?!

8
00:00:22,010 --> 00:00:24,330
And since it had to be something easy to build with sand,

9
00:00:24,330 --> 00:00:27,490
I thought about England and decided that Conwy Castle would be best.

10
00:00:27,490 --> 00:00:29,340
That's a surprising talent.

11
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:32,040
You fool!

12
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:35,080
If we ever get a chance to see women's swimsuits this close again,

13
00:00:35,080 --> 00:00:37,090
it'll probably only be in VR!

14
00:00:37,970 --> 00:00:39,600
Well, he's got a point.

15
00:00:40,090 --> 00:00:43,460
Usually, Shiori's buttons are done all the way up to the top,

16
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:44,600
but now, her chest is...

17
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,010
O gods, I thank you!

18
00:00:48,010 --> 00:00:49,980
Jiro-kun, are you all right?

19
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:52,500
Huh? Uh, yes! What is it?

20
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,490
I was thinking we should make a tunnel through this castle!

21
00:00:55,490 --> 00:00:57,690
We did it all the time when we were kids, remember?

22
00:00:57,690 --> 00:01:01,160
We'd dig in with our hands from either side and join together in the middle.

23
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,500
Join together?

24
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:06,560
Okay, come on. Slide it in gently. Go slow, okay?

25
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:07,250
Okay.

26
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:10,250
Um, maybe a little deeper?

27
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:14,260
Oh! There you are, Jiro-kun!

28
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,760
Look at us, playing with sand. It's like we went back in time.

29
00:01:21,190 --> 00:01:23,830
They're being all lovey over there. What the heck?

30
00:01:25,850 --> 00:01:31,720
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

31
00:01:40,950 --> 00:01:42,830
It's criminal to be so shy

32
00:01:42,830 --> 00:01:46,690
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

33
00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:49,000
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

34
00:01:50,010 --> 00:01:52,280
No less than supreme

35
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:55,690
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

36
00:01:56,580 --> 00:01:58,300
The wild ringing of bells

37
00:01:59,330 --> 00:02:05,410
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

38
00:02:06,170 --> 00:02:09,090
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

39
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:14,640
A daydream that seems like fiction

40
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:17,680
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

41
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:20,100
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

42
00:02:20,410 --> 00:02:22,720
My heart hurts and hurts,

43
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:27,610
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

44
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:31,090
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

45
00:02:31,090 --> 00:02:33,410
Be brave, my darling

46
00:02:33,410 --> 00:02:35,990
It won't all be happy and fun

47
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:38,010
It's all up to us

48
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:40,220
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

49
00:02:40,220 --> 00:02:43,870
Please look my way, darling

50
00:02:44,890 --> 00:02:52,970
Please notice my pure love for you

51
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,000
Rock, paper, scissors!

52
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:02,300
Which means Akari and Yakuin are gonna go buy stuff!

53
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:04,250
What? Me and Jiro?

54
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:06,740
We're always together. That's boring!

55
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:08,790
Well, sorry you got stuck with me.

56
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,220
It's pretty crowded.

57
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:14,040
It seems like it's all guy-girl pairs.

58
00:03:14,370 --> 00:03:17,550
Being in a place filled with normies is getting old.

59
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:19,920
Today Couple's Discount
All items 20 yen off
It's gotta be because of this!

60
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,130
We should use it, too!

61
00:03:22,130 --> 00:03:24,430
What? But we're not a couple!

62
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,680
But being married counts, doesn't it?

63
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:31,940
You turned all red! I'll assume that means you're okay with it.

64
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,840
"Mock"! We're mock-married!

65
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:35,900
As long as no one finds out, it's fine!

66
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,440
Next customer!

67
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,810
Let's see... Three yakisobas, and...

68
00:03:40,810 --> 00:03:43,200
Couples can upgrade the size at no extra charge.

69
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,870
For real? That's so nice of you!

70
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:48,270
Then can we make all three of them larges?

71
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:51,170
I can't say no to a cute girlfriend like you!

72
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:53,800
You're one lucky boyfriend. I'm jealous!

73
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:58,270
Right, you're number 13. I'll call you when it's ready.

74
00:03:58,270 --> 00:03:59,710
Okay.

75
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,520
What was with that courtesy laugh?

76
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:06,030
Do things with more style, more like a boyfriend!

77
00:04:06,030 --> 00:04:09,720
Huh? What was I supposed to have done better, then?

78
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:13,970
Put your arm around my shoulders and say, "I'm proud to call her my girlfriend!"

79
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:15,980
It'd be like a dream to hear that.

80
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:19,010
Minami-kun might have done it if he were here.

81
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:21,990
That stuff doesn't just come out of nowhere.

82
00:04:21,990 --> 00:04:23,980
Customer number 13!

83
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:25,990
I'll go get it.

84
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:29,150
What was that? He's so infuriating!

85
00:04:29,150 --> 00:04:30,840
Hey, you alone?

86
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,810
Oh, crap. Where were we a minute ago?

87
00:04:38,270 --> 00:04:39,900
Does Akari know him?

88
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,010
I can't tell!

89
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,880
Jiro, over here!

90
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:46,890
What? You were waiting for a guy?

91
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:49,830
You're two totally different types. That's hilarious!

92
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:52,190
Um, are you acquaintances of hers?

93
00:04:52,190 --> 00:04:55,890
Ding, ding, ding! Acquaintances! We just became acquainted!

94
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,900
You know they're not! They're hitting on me!

95
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,150
Yeah, of course...

96
00:05:03,780 --> 00:05:06,460
Hey, bro, you're here with her, right?

97
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:09,910
Will you tell us her name?

98
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,660
We've asked, but she won't tell us.

99
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:15,910
Hey, are you staying somewhere around here tonight? Is it close?

100
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:20,800
U-Um, would you mind letting her go? She doesn't like what you're doing.

101
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,480
Oh, here it comes!

102
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:24,240
You after this girl, too?

103
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,920
No, um...

104
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:28,960
She's a little intense for you, ain't she, bro?

105
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,430
You look like a virgin, though. Are you?

106
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,440
Sh-She's my wife.

107
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,810
What?!

108
00:05:40,810 --> 00:05:42,440
She's married?!

109
00:05:43,140 --> 00:05:44,900
Sorry, bro!

110
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,200
Yeah, uh... Be happy together!

111
00:05:50,970 --> 00:05:53,450
L-Listen, Jiro...

112
00:05:53,990 --> 00:05:54,870
I'm sorry!
Huh?

113
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:58,610
I couldn't think up a lie on the spot,

114
00:05:58,610 --> 00:06:02,000
and I figured you must've hated being called my wife...

115
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,960
B-But calling you my girlfriend would've been... you know...

116
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:06,850
You are seriously infuriating!

117
00:06:06,850 --> 00:06:08,470
I said I'm sorry!

118
00:06:08,470 --> 00:06:11,120
I never said I hated it!

119
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,970
Huh?

120
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:14,360
I-I didn't say that, did I?

121
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,610
Don't just assume things like that.

122
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:21,230
Y-You were so cool... and then you ruined it, you idiot.

123
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:25,730
If you're always like that, you'll never get a girlfriend!

124
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:29,550
Don't apologize for everything.

125
00:06:29,550 --> 00:06:32,020
I feel like a loser for letting my heart race.

126
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:33,740
And in the practical, too...

127
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:37,750
Show me you're man enough to use me for practice.

128
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,000
F-For practice?

129
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,490
You get it now? Okay, so let's head back!

130
00:06:42,490 --> 00:06:43,500
Wh-Wha...

131
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:46,100
Hey! Quit pushing!

132
00:06:46,100 --> 00:06:48,880
They're gonna tease us for taking so long because of you.

133
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:50,730
It wasn't my fault!

134
00:06:50,730 --> 00:06:52,640
Walk faster!

135
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,720
I can't deal with that kind of thing...

136
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:02,720
This is paradise.

137
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:05,240
Don't talk like an old man.

138
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,150
This is so nostalgic. It feels like a school trip.

139
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:13,280
Mei-chan, you're not sunburned, are you?

140
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:16,060
No, I rubbed some oil on, so I'm fine.

141
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,910
But I guess a day isn't enough to even out a tan.

142
00:07:19,180 --> 00:07:22,670
Oh, the tan lines around here are fading, though.

143
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,730
Y-You've tanned some, too!

144
00:07:25,730 --> 00:07:28,700
You're right! And I put on sunblock and everything.

145
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,670
Come on, let's hurry up and get in.

146
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,680
So then I asked him,

147
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:39,680
"And how many kilos do you think you've gained since we started dating?"

148
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:44,020
It's impossible to stay the "perfect girl" 24 hours a day, right?

149
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,390
That's so not okay.

150
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:48,480
You're working hard to stay beautiful, and he just doesn't get it.

151
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,270
Bet he'll never get married.

152
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,950
Yeah, for real.

153
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,950
We can hear them talking.

154
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:57,860
Anyway, since we're on the subject, how's it going at your place, Akari?

155
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:59,090
Indeed.

156
00:07:59,090 --> 00:07:59,950
My place?

157
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:03,710
That virgin seems like he'd have unrealistic dreams about girls.

158
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:07,120
She complained about him all the time at first.

159
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:10,740
And you thought there was no way it could last this long.

160
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:14,220
Th-That's because he's super, uber sloppy!

161
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,970
So he's sloppy at home...

162
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:21,760
Doesn't Virgin-kun actually treat you better since he's got so little experience?

163
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:24,630
In the end, it's all about kindness, right?

164
00:08:24,630 --> 00:08:26,980
If he isn't kind, it won't feel good anyway.

165
00:08:26,980 --> 00:08:28,620
Like my ex before my last ex...

166
00:08:28,620 --> 00:08:32,950
Before we'd do it, I seriously thought about reading my mental notes aloud to him.

167
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:34,490
Hey, um...

168
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:37,140
We can hear everything you're saying. You okay with that?

169
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:40,240
It's totally fine! Actually, Hamano-san, you should join in!

170
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:42,060
You, too, Sakurazaka-san!

171
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:43,070
Huh?

172
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:45,390
How do your relationship chats usually go?

173
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,500
I... I, um...

174
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:52,790
After hearing what you said, I think it's all about caring for someone.

175
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:56,920
It's sort of a way to give yourself the feeling that you really like them,

176
00:08:56,920 --> 00:09:00,510
and I'd like to believe the other party wants to feel seen, too.

177
00:09:00,810 --> 00:09:03,000
It's not about being good or bad at it.

178
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,400
It's wanting to make eye contact even one more time.

179
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:08,220
I think I like that kind of thing.

180
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:11,780
Well said!

181
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:13,140
That's it, exactly!

182
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:15,530
I want to really feel that I'm loved.

183
00:09:15,530 --> 00:09:18,870
Hamano-san, will you marry me?

184
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,980
Why are you clinging to me like that?

185
00:09:20,980 --> 00:09:23,980
C'mon, cut it out!
Sorry for talking about this right now.

186
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:27,540
Huh? Oh, no, it's fine. I'm the one who should apologize.

187
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:32,720
I, um... I don't have much experience, so I couldn't join the conversation, that's all.

188
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,400
Really? But you're super cute!

189
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:38,550
But I get it. It's hard to jump into a conversation like that.

190
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:43,170
When it comes to the stuff they were talking about, I'm no match for those two.

191
00:09:43,170 --> 00:09:45,330
I-It's very educational.

192
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:48,560
You're so serious!

193
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,290
If it were Jiro-kun...
If it was Jiro...

194
00:09:57,810 --> 00:09:59,070
Akari!

195
00:09:59,450 --> 00:10:01,270
We're gonna head back first.

196
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:02,330
Okay.

197
00:10:04,950 --> 00:10:06,830
Women

198
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:08,330
Men

199
00:10:08,740 --> 00:10:10,610
Was the men's bath pretty big?

200
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,380
Uh... yeah, kinda.

201
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:13,970
O-Oh, cool.

202
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:17,600
Hey, you got burned.

203
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,840
I know, right?

204
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:22,880
The shower hurt like hell. Especially the back of my neck.

205
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,850
Hang on a sec. I should have...

206
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,850
Come here. I'll put it on for you.

207
00:10:28,180 --> 00:10:28,860
Huh?

208
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:32,110
Wow, it's really noticeable!

209
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:35,340
U-Um, don't you need to get back to your room?

210
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:37,790
What's that supposed to mean? Do you want me to leave?

211
00:10:37,790 --> 00:10:38,610
No, just...

212
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:41,580
It might look weird if we're together too long.

213
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:43,770
They might start teasing us.

214
00:10:44,890 --> 00:10:46,620
You worry too much.

215
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:49,680
Wait, so your neck isn't ticklish, huh?

216
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:53,880
I guess not. I never really had any ticklish spots.

217
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,500
Then how about here?

218
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:59,090
Whoa! It's not ticklish? For real?

219
00:10:59,090 --> 00:11:01,740
Get off me! What if someone sees us?

220
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:11,020
We haven't done this yet today.

221
00:11:11,020 --> 00:11:13,350
W-We're not doing the practical right now...

222
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:17,280
But ever since we got here, there's been this distance between us.

223
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,530
It makes me feel weird.

224
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:23,030
Please... just be the way you always...

225
00:11:23,030 --> 00:11:24,320
Akari!

226
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:25,030
Oh.

227
00:11:25,910 --> 00:11:27,310
Were you in the middle of something?

228
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:30,790
Nope! I was just telling Jiro he should treat me to a drink.

229
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:33,000
I think I'll have apple juice.

230
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,960
Hey! I never said I'd buy you anything!

231
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:37,080
Oh, really? I'll have a cola.

232
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,550
Would you look at this? Seriously, I am so done with him.

233
00:11:42,550 --> 00:11:46,380
So, Takamiya-san... You wanted a cola, right?

234
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:48,200
Yeah. Thanks!

235
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:51,340
Aka—Watanabe, what did you say you wanted?

236
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,560
Watanabe...

237
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,430
Apple juice.

238
00:11:57,430 --> 00:11:58,360
Right.

239
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,860
Thanks!

240
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:04,070
So, he's like a major no, right?

241
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:08,250
Uh-oh. I stepped on some kind of land mine.

242
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:10,480
I hope nothing bad happens...

243
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,080
Watanabe Akari
Time starts now
10 minutes
The beach shop

244
00:12:17,780 --> 00:12:18,840
You will come.

245
00:12:20,070 --> 00:12:20,920
Yes, I will.

246
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:27,050
Hey, where's Akari?

247
00:12:27,590 --> 00:12:29,600
She said she was going to the convenience store.

248
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:33,120
What? But I thought we were going to play cards.

249
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:35,060
Do you know where Jiro-chan is?

250
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,520
He said he was going to go wander around.

251
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:40,070
What? Are any shops still open?

252
00:12:40,070 --> 00:12:42,510
At this hour, probably just the convenience store.

253
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:43,570
Sheesh...

254
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:46,070
Shall we? For a change of pace.

255
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:55,620
Um, I'm very sorry.

256
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:56,880
There it is.

257
00:12:56,880 --> 00:13:00,920
You don't know why I'm angry, but you start off with an apology anyway. Like always.

258
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:03,090
Yes. I don't know why you're angry.

259
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,570
I'm very sorry.

260
00:13:04,570 --> 00:13:08,090
I'm telling you not to apologize when you don't know the reason for it!

261
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:09,240
Are you stupid?!

262
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,350
Y-Yes!

263
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:12,970
I'm sor—Okay!

264
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:19,110
Whoa, what?! What are you...

265
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,040
That swimsuit...

266
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,900
I've been looking forward to it.

267
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:29,620
I got to come to the ocean with you, even if it's for work.

268
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,370
So she meant what she said?

269
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:36,400
But you just keep worrying about how other people see us.

270
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,350
When I do talk to you, you're cold toward me.

271
00:13:38,350 --> 00:13:40,760
It's like I'm the only one excited about this.

272
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,380
I hate it so much.

273
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:45,630
She hates it? But that...

274
00:13:46,180 --> 00:13:48,890
That makes it sound like she's jealous.

275
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:51,890
No, it's nothing, really.

276
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:54,710
Am I stupid? I can't get the wrong idea.

277
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:56,680
It's just her usual "I hate it" syndrome.

278
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,140
Anyway!

279
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:02,690
I know you don't want people to see you with me, but...

280
00:14:02,690 --> 00:14:04,580
No! It's not that!

281
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:05,900
Yes, it is!

282
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,650
I'm telling you, it's not!

283
00:14:08,070 --> 00:14:09,660
It's the other way around.

284
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:14,260
Being around a plain, boring guy like me is just embarrassing for you, isn't it?

285
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:16,550
Huh? Why should that matter?

286
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:18,790
Who I hang out with is up to me.

287
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:21,310
People like me worry about that kind of thing!

288
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:24,300
Even if you're okay with it, other people might think things.

289
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,170
And it's not like we have to spend time together right now—

290
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:34,560
Why do you have to say sad things like that?

291
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:38,400
Look at me more, like you do when we're at home.

292
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:41,540
Come on... Look.

293
00:14:46,070 --> 00:14:47,820
Look! Look!

294
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:51,100
When we're at home, all you do is stare at my chest, you moron!
Ow, ow, ow!

295
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:56,180
I already know about all that, so don't try to act cool when we're out here!

296
00:14:56,180 --> 00:14:58,580
The pressure! All kinds of pressure!

297
00:14:58,580 --> 00:15:00,060
Calm down, Akari!

298
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:01,800
Just let go for a minute! Okay?

299
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,670
You won't get your message across this way.

300
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,840
Come on. Look me in the eye and talk to me.

301
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:08,450
Yeah... Okay.

302
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:10,470
I'm glad she's so docile today.

303
00:15:10,470 --> 00:15:13,700
I hate that we're not a married couple when we're outside the house.

304
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,970
I hate you acting cold and calling me by my last name.

305
00:15:16,660 --> 00:15:19,980
When I see you talking with those other girls all the time...

306
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:23,610
It's like you're not my husband anymore.

307
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:25,020
I can't help thinking,

308
00:15:25,020 --> 00:15:28,240
what if even after we're back home, we aren't a married couple anymore?

309
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:30,490
And I hate feeling like that!

310
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:36,500
Um, is it okay for me to ask what you mean by that?

311
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:39,370
What do you mean, "what do I mean"? I don't get it.

312
00:15:39,660 --> 00:15:42,540
Well, like... How do I put it...

313
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:45,190
You want to be together even when we're out,

314
00:15:45,190 --> 00:15:47,750
y-you want me to call you by your first name,

315
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:51,800
and you hate it when I talk to other girls... right?

316
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:52,880
It's like...

317
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:58,270
I can't help thinking that... those are things a jealous girlfriend might say.

318
00:15:58,990 --> 00:16:00,620
Wait, what? For real?

319
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:02,890
Y-You're not making sense!

320
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:04,500
What do you mean, "for real"?

321
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,970
Well, I mean...

322
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:08,400
Jealous? Like hell I am!

323
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:12,040
M-More like I'm angry because you act like I'm just a convenience!

324
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,910
That's what she meant?!

325
00:16:14,390 --> 00:16:17,120
For now, I'll make sure to call you by your first name.

326
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:19,590
You should've just said that from the start.

327
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:22,160
Wow! The moon's beautiful tonight!

328
00:16:22,550 --> 00:16:24,730
It's brighter than I thought it'd be.

329
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:26,420
The breeze feels so nice!

330
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,620
Oh, by the way, I was watching a drama on TV yesterday,

331
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:35,430
and there was a girl who looked like you.

332
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:37,680
Oh, the one playing the younger sister?

333
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:39,430
Yeah! Do you get compared to her a lot?

334
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:41,430
What do I do now?

335
00:16:41,430 --> 00:16:44,840
It's too cramped in here. Scoot over that way!

336
00:16:46,290 --> 00:16:48,380
You're the one who dragged me in here!

337
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:49,190
Shh!

338
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:54,690
This sucks. I just want to get out of here already.

339
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:56,300
How is complaining gonna help?

340
00:16:56,300 --> 00:17:00,120
Right now, we just have to make sure Shiori and Hamano don't see us.

341
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,700
That's always where you end up.

342
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,560
Did you say something?

343
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:04,690
Nope, nothing.

344
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:07,960
It took a lot to wear this swimsuit...

345
00:17:08,450 --> 00:17:10,210
But even when we're this close,

346
00:17:10,590 --> 00:17:13,130
in Jiro's heart, I don't even exist.

347
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:19,220
Back when all I did was chase after Minami-kun, I managed to be a lot more optimistic.

348
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:23,600
But now, every time it feels fun or reassuring to have Jiro beside me,

349
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:25,730
I get scared that he'll leave.

350
00:17:27,310 --> 00:17:28,750
Even right now,

351
00:17:28,750 --> 00:17:33,230
I can feel that Jiro really cares for Sakurazaka-san.

352
00:17:33,230 --> 00:17:36,910
It's something I've known about since we first met,

353
00:17:36,910 --> 00:17:38,960
but I still feel all muddled.

354
00:17:39,570 --> 00:17:40,740
I really hate this.

355
00:17:41,550 --> 00:17:43,660
Akari? Are you feeling sick?

356
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:47,500
Really? That's a relief.

357
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,250
It's hot, but can you hang in there just a little longer?

358
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,510
If I do, what then?

359
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:55,510
What do you mean?

360
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,350
You'll be able to leave?

361
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:06,020
Do you hear someone talking?

362
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,640
S-Stop that! Don't scare me!

363
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:14,380
You really can't stand that kind of thing, huh?

364
00:18:15,210 --> 00:18:16,530
What if there's...

365
00:18:16,530 --> 00:18:18,940
a ghost or something over there?

366
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:20,280
Mei-chan!

367
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:28,040
Huh? There's no one here.

368
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:33,370
Sorry about that. My mistake.

369
00:18:33,370 --> 00:18:34,800
Thank goodness.

370
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:37,360
Maybe what I heard came from the road...

371
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:38,800
Safe!

372
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:45,830
Ow!

373
00:18:45,830 --> 00:18:46,810
Hey, are you nuts?!

374
00:18:46,810 --> 00:18:48,590
Quit banging around!

375
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:53,860
Mei-chan, let's go back now!

376
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:55,120
Hurry! Hurry!

377
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:56,070
Wait...

378
00:18:59,820 --> 00:19:02,320
This seriously sucks.

379
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:05,030
Come on, get off of me already.

380
00:19:05,030 --> 00:19:07,830
I can't believe you'd ogle my chest in an emergency like this.

381
00:19:07,830 --> 00:19:09,830
That's so wrong.

382
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:12,170
I swear, that's how all guys are.

383
00:19:12,170 --> 00:19:14,000
I regret wearing this swimsuit.

384
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,640
You wanted me to look, didn't you?

385
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:20,530
Th-That was just... something I said in the moment.

386
00:19:20,530 --> 00:19:23,850
And you need to hurry up and forget that!

387
00:19:23,850 --> 00:19:25,590
Oh, I get it.

388
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:28,440
So you were just toying with me, is that it?

389
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,350
No, it's not—

390
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:31,060
Yes, it is.

391
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:34,360
Wanting me to use your first name in public, getting mad at me earlier...

392
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:36,610
If you just said all that "in the moment,"

393
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,110
then I'm not gonna change a thing.

394
00:19:55,710 --> 00:19:57,630
I hate you, Jiro.

395
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:01,130
I hate this. I'm so embarrassed. I'm gonna die.

396
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:08,140
Hey, what's wrong? It's too hot for this.

397
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:11,310
Come on, it's all clear. We can get out of here now.

398
00:20:12,910 --> 00:20:16,400
And your knee is poking me. Can you move it?

399
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:19,070
That's... not my knee.

400
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:21,920
Wh-What?

401
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:22,900
I'm serious.

402
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:24,410
You're kidding...

403
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:25,910
Sorry.

404
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:30,050
Raise your face up.

405
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,820
Hey, Jiro...

406
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,170
Did looking at me make that happen?

407
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:47,180
What? W-Wait!

408
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:48,930
W-We can't! We can't!

409
00:20:48,930 --> 00:20:52,420
Jiro, we can't! Th-There's an order to these kinds of things!

410
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,440
Huh?

411
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,290
Jiro?!

412
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:03,040
They said it's mild heatstroke. Are you okay?

413
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:04,150
Yeah.

414
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:06,160
Hey, so...

415
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:13,160
Sorry. I heard that you went and got people to carry me.

416
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:16,670
Also, um... sorry about all that other stuff, too.

417
00:21:16,670 --> 00:21:18,920
Didn't I tell you not to apologize?

418
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:21,170
It makes me feel worse.

419
00:21:21,170 --> 00:21:23,790
I'm telling you not to apologize!

420
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:24,920
And also!

421
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:28,610
"You wanted me to look, didn't you?" What was with that tone?

422
00:21:28,610 --> 00:21:30,160
It's unbelievable!

423
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,220
All those times you stole glances at home?

424
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:34,310
I was letting you look because I felt sorry for you!

425
00:21:34,310 --> 00:21:36,160
You should be grateful to me, idiot!

426
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:38,190
You're too loud! Keep it down!

427
00:21:38,190 --> 00:21:40,450
Instead of just that kind of stuff,

428
00:21:40,450 --> 00:21:44,190
I want you to look at all the different parts of me.

429
00:21:44,190 --> 00:21:46,610
We've already been married for four months,

430
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:50,070
but I don't know anything about you yet.

431
00:21:50,070 --> 00:21:54,700
I-I mean, knowing about each other will make living together more fun, right?

432
00:21:55,070 --> 00:21:59,020
I want to see and know all the different parts of you, too.

433
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:01,350
Since we're still married and all.

434
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:02,090
Okay?

435
00:22:02,970 --> 00:22:03,820
Sure.

436
00:22:04,710 --> 00:22:09,520
As I looked at Akari smiling and saying, "It's already been four months,"

437
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,760
I thought a lot of different things...

438
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:19,000
But something about the way she said "still" stuck in an odd spot and stayed that way.

439
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:24,000
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

440
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:28,430
I want to give love a try

441
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:31,340
In this night when everything begins to overflow

442
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:33,610
I match my stride to yours

443
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:39,450
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

444
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:44,020
The answers always slip away

445
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:47,440
All I want is to do it over again

446
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:52,840
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

447
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:57,140
I want to know where my heart is hiding

448
00:22:57,140 --> 00:23:01,920
One day this will end

449
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:04,720
I know that

450
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,430
And I know the signs of discord

451
00:23:06,430 --> 00:23:08,480
Turn them inside out

452
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:10,080
Don't let them pile up

453
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:14,290
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

454
00:23:14,290 --> 00:23:18,330
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

455
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:22,760
I want to give love a try

456
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,780
Everything begins to overflow

457
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,970
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

458
00:23:27,970 --> 00:23:36,230
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

459
00:23:50,730 --> 00:23:52,410
Knock, knock! Let's play cards!

460
00:23:52,410 --> 00:23:53,220
Let's do it!

461
00:23:53,220 --> 00:23:54,570
You can come in!

462
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:58,580
Old Maid? Sevens? Whoever loses gets a penalty!

463
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:01,040
Okay!

464
00:24:03,740 --> 00:24:05,720
This face pack feels great!

465
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:06,590
Right?

466
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:10,090
Next Time
More Than a Confession, but Not Yet a Broken Heart.
Next time, "More Than a Confession, but Not Yet a Broken Heart."

